title: Biplots — biplots
text: model Output `bayes_ammi()`. contain results Bayesian AMMI model, including sampled iterations. burnin Numeric. Percentage iterations discard burn-avoid effects random initializations sampling. example, `burnin = 0.1` removes first 10% iterations. thin Numeric. Proportion sampled iterations retain analysis. example, `thin = 0.2` keeps 20% iterations, selecting 1 every 5 iterations. pb Numeric. Significance levels contours plot. Smaller values `pb` result wider contours, higher values create smaller, specific contours. plot_stable Logical. `TRUE`, stable instances highlighted output plot. plot_unstable Logical. `TRUE`, unstable instances highlighted output plot. ncolors Integer. Specifies number distinct colors use plot. Adjust control visual differentiation elements plot.

title: Biplots — biplots
text: list following components: plot plot displaying contours final biplot values. contour_data `data.frame` containing data used create contours. biplot_data `data.frame` containing data used recreate final biplot values.
